-- Alcoa Quebec Workers Accept Conciliator’s Report, Union Says
-- B y   F r e d e r i c   T o m e s c o
-- 2013-02-22T17:17:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-22/alcoa-quebec-workers-accept-conciliator-s-report-union-says.html
Alcoa Inc. (AA)  workers at the aluminum
producer’s ABI smelter in Quebec accepted a proposed five-year
labor contract, the United Steelworkers union said.  The accord covers 944 workers and includes a 13 percent
wage increase over the five years, the union said today in a
 statement  on its website. The contract includes an improved
healthcare insurance package, the union said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Frederic Tomesco in Montreal at 
 tomesco@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
